r costs or the insurance excess.</p><p class="document-bullet">**Demand for Remedy:**</p><p class="document-paragraph">Please respond in writing within 7 days from the date of this letter, confirming your agreement to provide the compensation demanded. Failure to respond satisfactorily by the deadline will result in escalation to Consumer Affairs Victoria and potentially to the Victorian Civil and Administrative Tribunal (VCAT).</p><p class="document-paragraph">I trust you will address this matter promptly and professionally to avoid further action.</p><p class="document-paragraph">Yours sincerely,</p><p class="document-signature">[Signature]</p><p class="document-paragraph">awdawd  </p><p class="document-paragraph">[Your Contact Information]  </p><p class="document-bullet">---</p><p class="document-paragraph">Please ensure you fill in any missing details before sending the letter. This document is intended to assert your rights under the Australian Consumer Law and seek resolution for the damage caused during the servicing of your vehicle.</p>
    
